reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 11, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Beyond adorable. A little gal's fav dream stroller for her dolls. The plus, it holds two baby dolls, easy to assemble, good quality, vibrant red color. Def great economical stroller toy. Good purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Made our little girl happy!
reviews.reviewText: It seemed like a good little stroller. I took it out of box to check it. Did not see it in action though.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 11, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Got this for my kiddo who likes to take her friends on *adventures*. It was super easy to put together, and so far, has held up really well! It's super cute, has taken a bit of a beating between her and her older brothers, and she loves that she can fit so many in it. It is also fairly compact, and even folds up if you need it to.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Very cute stroller and good quality for the price
reviews.reviewText: Very cute stroller and good quality for the price. I love that they close up for storage and taking with us. My only complaint is that they sent 2 of the left side (that you use to lock the stroller open) instead of a right and a left. It works but doesn't clip into place.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Looks like an adult stroller. Just like moms
reviews.reviewText: Folds up just like moms for easy storage. Holds two of her babies. My 4 year old granddaughter loved it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not great for a 2 yr old.
reviews.reviewText: The stroller is cute. But, it is difficult for a toddler to keep two dolls in the stroller. The front seat is flimsy and the seat belt is all that holds the doll in. That is as long as the toddler doesn't tip the stroller. (lLike she just did) It wasn't as sturdy as expected. I don't think it will last a long time. My daughter-n-law got a better cheaper one doll stroller at a common big chain store. I got this because she was trying to fit two dolls in the one doll stroller. Wouldn't buy again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Granddaughter loved this for Christmas so she could use it for her twin reborn babies. Good quality

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Not impressed at all
reviews.reviewText: Very disappointed with this stroller considering how much we paid for it. It’s possible we got a stroller that was returned since the box was taped up. But the instructions to put it together are complicated and does not make any sense. The frame we got appears to be bent like someone tried to put it together already. We tried for over 30 minutes and could not get it to work. Will be sending back.You should consider better instructions.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on August 11, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Tricky to assemble. One of the popper buttons fell off straight away.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on September 20, 2020
reviews.reviewText: Easy to put together, seems quite durable. Easy for small children to manoeuvre and corner. Similar enough to an adults that she’s happy with it! Only issue is that the seat covers come off each time she puts the baby in and out at the back
